The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Karim: Want to win every trophy
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Karim: Want to win every trophy
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohun Bagans Moroccan coach Karim Bencherifa on Monday declared that his target would be to make the green-and-maroon brigade champions in every tournament they play.         
	The 40-year old former Churchill Brothers coach, who started his assignment with the city giants on Monday, was addressing a news conference after his maiden training session at the club ground.         
	I am honoured to be Bagans coach The national club of India The club has a separate identity. I feel proud, was Karims answer when asked why he chose Mohun Bagan.         
	I am a professional and I look at the job as a package. Its about a team, a squad, the quality of a club and the monetary package. But the craze for football in Calcutta has brought me here, he said.         
	I want to win every trophy But a coach is not a robot, he is a human being I have some plans, Karim said.         
	Talking about the squad that was announced on the day with Bhaichung Bhutia still the captain, Karim said: It is a well balanced squad and we have a strong bench  the most important thing in a long season.         
	On his plans to handle the two superstars in the team  Brazilian Jose Ramirez Barreto and Bhaichung Bhutia  the coach, who plans to host a nine-day residential camp at Durgapur, said: They are assets for any team.         
	Players like them are an added advantage. I am here to ease relations between seniors and juniors.                                                                                                                          
